---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import CardAlternate from '../components/CardAlternate.astro';
import Resources from '../components/Resources.astro'
---
<Layout>
  <main class="m-auto p-4 max-w-full text-xl sm:px-24">
    <span class="columns-2 flex md:shrink-0 justify-items-center items-center justify-evenly">
        <h1 class="text-mech-500 pt-40 content-center font-bold font-sans sm:px-9 bg-clip-text text-5xl text-center sm:text-8xl">Mental Health Resources!</h1>
    </span>
    <Resources/>
    <h2 class="text-mech-500 pt-12 pb-4 content-center font-bold font-sans bg-clip-text text-4xl sm:text-6xl">Tips to De-stress & Reduce Anxiety üíô</h2>
    <p class="text-mech-500 leading-10">Check in with yourself regularly. Try out our tips below; if you need someone to talk to, please scroll down!
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-mech-500 py-6 content-center font-bold font-sans bg-clip-text text-2xl sm:text-3xl">Quick Check List</h3>
      <ol class="list-inside list-decimal py-2">
        <li>Does what I‚Äôm hearing in my head create a negative emotion in my mind?</li>
        <li>Why is this thought making me feel a negative emotion?</li>
        <li>Does this thought make sense?</li>
      </ol>
If this thought likely doesn‚Äôt make sense, and is likely not to occur, <span class="font-bold">abandon thought.</span>
      <br/>
      <br/>
    <h3 class="text-mech-500 pt-6 pb-4 content-center font-bold font-sans bg-clip-text text-2xl sm:text-3xl">Try the following:</h3>
      <ol class="list-inside list-decimal py-2">
        <li>Listen to your favourite songs</li>
        <li>Talk to loved ones</li>
        <li>Do a fun activity</li>
        <li>Purchase a fidget toy (e.g. fidget spinner, tangle, rubik‚Äôs cube, putty, spaghetti ball, stress ball, flappy chain)</li>
        <li>Invest time into mindful minutes, a helpful tool includes the mobile app ‚ÄúHeadspace‚Äù</li>
      <li>Read a book</li>
      </ol>
    <span class="font-bold">Remember, a proven way to quickly get rid of stress is to maximize time in a ‚Äúflow‚Äù activity - any activity where you feel completely immersed throughout.</span>
</p>
    <h2 class="text-mech-500 pt-12 pb-8 content-center font-bold font-sans bg-clip-text text-4xl sm:text-6xl">On-Campus Resources</h2>
    <ul role="list" class="link-card-grid grid gap-8">
      <Card
              href="https://studentlife.utoronto.ca/department/health-wellness/"
        title="Health & Wellness Centre: 416-978-8030, info.hwc@utoronto.ca"
        body="Physical and mental health services, stress workshops, certain immunizations, sexual health consultations, and nutrition counseling."
      />
      <Card
              href="https://studentlife.utoronto.ca/service/myssp/"
              title="U of T My Student Support Program (My SSP): 1-844-451-9700 (Outside of North America, call 001-416-380-6578)"
              body=" Confidential, free, 24-hour chat support for any school, health, or general life concern."
      />
    </ul>
    <ul role="list" class="link-card-grid grid pt-4 gap-8">
      <CardAlternate
              href="https://good2talk.ca/ontario/"
              title="Good2Talk Student Helpline: 1-866-925-5454"
              body="Confidential, free, 24-hour counselling chat system for mental health and addiction."
      />
      <CardAlternate
              href="https://gersteincentre.org/"
              title="Gerstein Crisis Centre: 416-929-5200"
              body="A 24-hour community based centre for those in crisis due to mental health issues or substance use."
      />
    </ul>
    <h2 class="text-mech-500 pt-12 pb-8 content-center font-bold font-sans bg-clip-text text-4xl sm:text-6xl">Off-Campus Resources</h2>
    <ul role="list" class="link-card-grid grid gap-8">
      <Card
              href="http://www.camh.ca/"
              title="The Centre for Addiction and Mental Health (CAMH): 416-535-8501, press 2"
              body="Critical mental health assistance for various mental disorders and substance use."
      />
      <Card
        href="https://kidshelpphone.ca/"
              title="Kids Help Phone: 1-800-668-6868"
              body="National service that offers anonymous, free counselling, 24/7 through text, on the phone, or on their website."
      />
    </ul>
    <ul role="list" class="link-card-grid pt-4 grid gap-8">
      <CardAlternate
              href="https://togetherall.com/en-ca/"
              title="TogetherAll"
              body="An anonymous, online peer-to-peer support community for common mental health issues."
      />
      <CardAlternate
        href="https://www.dcogt.com/home-support"
              title="Distress Centres of Greater Toronto: 416-408-HELP (4357)"
              body="Chat lines for people experiencing various difficulties."
      />
    </ul>
    <ul role="list" class="link-card-grid grid pt-4 gap-8">
      <Card
              href="https://www.awhl.org/home"
              title="Assaulted Women's Helpline: 416-863-0511"
              body="24-hour telephone crisis line to all women who have experienced abuse, providing counselling, emotional support, information and referralsl."
      />
      <Card
        href="https://www.torontocentralhealthline.ca/displayservice.aspx?id=133949"
              title="Central Intake Shelter (Housing): 416-338-4766"
              body="This is the centralized system for city-managed temporary shelters, where homeless individuals can go to determine their next steps."
      />
    </ul>
    <ul role="list" class="link-card-grid grid pt-4 gap-8">
      <CardAlternate
              href="https://www.connexontario.ca/"
              title="ConnexOntario: 1-866-531-2600"
              body="Free and confidential 24/7 health services information for people experiencing problems with alcohol and drugs, mental illness and/or gambling."
      />
      <CardAlternate
        href="https://www.crisisservicescanada.ca/en/"
              title="Crisis Services Canada (Canada Suicide Prevention): 1-833-456-4566"
              body="National network of various crisis helplines (especially )."
      />
    </ul>
  </main>
</Layout>

